{
  "doc_id": "30641",
  "text": "NAION is known to be a consequence of acute ischemia of the optic nerve head, but the precise mechanism of the disease is unclear and presumably is multifactorial, including the development of a compartment syndrome [CITATION_1] , embolism, and vascular dysregulation [CITATION_2] . Recently, early inf lammation components were determined in clinical NAION and its models [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . NAION results in early cytokine mediated changes [CITATION_6] , and then sequential inflammatory cellular activation and infiltration are observed [CITATION_7] .",
